 long since worn down, feeling myself a ghost despite the idiotic substantiality of the insulators, I shall again come out of that station and without visible companions walk along the footpath that accompanies the highway the ten or so versts to Leshino. One after another the telegraph poles will hum at my approach. A crow will settle on a boulderâ€”settle and straighten a wing that has folded wrong. The day will probably be on the grayish side. Changes in the appearance of the surrounding land